{"title_page": "Hell-On", "text_new": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = Hell-On\n| type       = Studio\n| artist     = [[Neko Case]]\n| cover      = Neko Case - Hell-On.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = {{Start date|2018|06|01|mf=yes}}\n| recorded   = {{ubl|Carnacial Singing, St.|{{small|([[St. Johnsbury, Vermont|St. Johnsbury]], [[Vermont|VT]])}}\n|Ingrid Studios|{{small|([[Stockholm]], [[Sweden|SE]])}}\n|WaveLab Studio|{{small|([[Tucson, Arizona|Tucson]], [[Arizona|AZ]])}}}}\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      =\n| length     = {{Duration|m=52|s=44}}\n| label      = [[Anti- (record label)|Anti-]]\n| producer   = [[Neko Case]], [[Bj\u00f6rn Yttling]]\n| prev_title = [[The Worse Things Get, the Harder I Fight, the Harder I Fight, the More I Love You ]]\n| prev_year  = 2013\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n}}\n'''''Hell-On''''' is the seventh studio album by American singer-songwriter [[Neko Case]], released on June 1, 2018, on [[Anti- (record label)|Anti-]]. Case recorded the album largely in [[Stockholm]], co-producing with [[Bj\u00f6rn Yttling]] of [[Peter Bjorn and John]].<ref name=\"tragedy\">{{cite news |last=Abdurraqib |first=Hanif |url= http://ew.com/music/2018/05/30/neko-case-hell-on-interview/ |title=Neko Case on her new album and moving on from tragedy: 'I've always been a person who fights' |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |date=May 30, 2018 |accessdate=June 1, 2018}}</ref>\n\nCase promoted the album by touring with [[Ray Lamontagne]].<ref name=\"lamontagne\">{{cite news |last=Varga |first=George |url= http://www.sandiegouniontribune.com/entertainment/music/sd-et-artscal-neko-case-20180527-story.html |title=Neko Case, armed with new album, 'Hell-On,' is SDSU-bound with Ray Lamontagne |work=[[San Diego Union-Tribune]] |date=May 27, 2018 |accessdate=May 30, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\n{{Album ratings\n| ADM = 7.9/10<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.anydecentmusic.com/review/9367/Neko-Case-Hell-On.aspx |title=Hell-On by Neko Case reviews |website=[[AnyDecentMusic?]] |accessdate=September 7, 2019}}</ref>\n| MC = 85/100<ref name=\"metacritic\">{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/music/hell-on/neko-case |title=Hell-On by Neko Case Reviews and Tracks |website=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=June 7, 2018}}</ref>\n| rev1 = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev1Score = {{Rating|4.5|5}}<ref name=\"allmusic\">{{cite web |url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/hell-on-mw0003156802 |title=Hell-On \u2013 Neko Case |website=[[AllMusic]] |accessdate=June 7, 2018 |last=Deming |first=Mark}}</ref>\n| rev2 = ''[[The A.V. Club]]''\n| rev2Score = A<ref>{{cite web |url=https://music.avclub.com/neko-case-is-a-force-of-nature-on-the-masterful-hell-on-1826374725 |title=Neko Case is a force of nature on the masterful Hell-On |work=[[The A.V. Club]] |date=May 31, 2018 |accessdate=June 8, 2018 |last=Rife |first=Katie}}</ref>\n| rev3 = ''[[Chicago Tribune]]''\n| rev3Score = {{Rating|3.5|4}}<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/entertainment/music/ct-ent-neko-case-hell-on-review-0605-story.html |title=Neko Case stomps the terra with the powerful \u2018Hell-On\u2019 |work=[[Chicago Tribune]] |date=June 1, 2018 |accessdate=June 8, 2018 |last=Kot |first=Greg |authorlink=Greg Kot}}</ref>\n| rev4 = ''[[The Guardian]]''\n| rev4Score = {{Rating|5|5}}<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2018/jun/01/neko-case-hell-on-review |title=Neko Case: Hell-On review \u2013 a pitch-perfect roar of female defiance |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=June 1, 2018 |accessdate=June 8, 2018 |last=Snapes |first=Laura}}</ref>\n| rev5 = ''[[The Independent]]''\n| rev5Score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/father-john-misty-new-album-review-gods-favorite-customer-roger-daltrey-laura-marling-a8375986.html |title=Album reviews: Father John Misty, Roger Daltrey, LUMP and more |work=[[The Independent]] |date=May 30, 2018 |accessdate=June 8, 2018 |last1=Kaplan |first1=Ilana |last2=Aubrey |first2=Elizabeth |last3=Morgan |first3=Jessica}}</ref>\n| rev6 = ''[[Mojo (magazine)|Mojo]]''\n| rev6Score = {{rating|3|5}}<ref>{{cite journal |title=Neko Case: Hell-On |work=[[Mojo (magazine)|Mojo]] |issue=296 |date=July 2018 |last=Nelson |first=Chris |page=88}}</ref>\n| rev7 = ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]''\n| rev7Score = 7.7/10<ref>{{cite web |url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/neko-case-hell-on/ |title=Neko Case: Hell-On |work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]] |date=June 5, 2018 |accessdate=June 8, 2018 |last=Sodomsky |first=Sam}}</ref>\n| rev8 = ''[[Q (magazine)|Q]]''\n| rev8Score = {{rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite journal |title=Neko Case: Hell-On |work=[[Q (magazine)|Q]] |issue=386 |date=July 2018 |last=Barton |first=Laura |page=108}}</ref>\n| rev9 = ''[[Rolling Stone]]''\n| rev9Score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/albumreviews/review-neko-cases-fierce-hell-on-is-one-of-her-best-w521135 |title=Review: Neko Case's Fierce 'Hell-On' Is One of Her Best |work=[[Rolling Stone]] |date=June 7, 2018 |accessdate=June 8, 2018 |last=Hermes |first=Will |authorlink=Will Hermes}}</ref>\n| rev10 = ''[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]''\n| rev10Score = B+<ref>{{cite web |url=https://noisey.vice.com/en_us/article/qvmdxd/expert-witness-with-robert-christgau-tuneyards-coutney-barnett-neko-case |title=Robert Christgau on Merrill Garbus's Creative Compulsions |work=[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]] |date=July 7, 2018 |accessdate=July 7, 2018 |last=Christgau |first=Robert |authorlink=Robert Christgau}}</ref>\n}}\n\n''Hell-On'' received universal acclaim from critics. At [[Metacritic]], which assigns a [[standard score|normalized]] rating out of 100 to reviews from mainstream publications, the album received an [[weighted arithmetic mean|average]] score of 85 based on 22 reviews.<ref name=\"metacritic\"/>\n\nIn the review for [[AllMusic]], critic Mark Deming praised the album; \"With ''Hell-On'', Case has once again given herself an ideal showcase for her talents as a vocalist, songwriter, and producer; it's lush but intimate, and one of the strongest and most satisfying records she's delivered to date. Which, given her catalog, says a great deal.\"<ref name=\"allmusic\"/>\n\n==Accolades==\n{|class=\"sortable wikitable\"\n|-\n! Publication\n! Accolade\n! Rank\n! class=\"unsortable\"|{{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| ''[[The A.V. Club]]''\n| Top 20 Albums of 2018\n| {{center|2}}\n| {{center|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://music.avclub.com/the-a-v-club-s-20-best-albums-of-2018-1831107874|title=The A.V. Club's 20 Best Albums of 2018|website=[[The A.V. Club]]|last1=Purdom|first1=Clayton|last2=McLevy|first2=Alex|date=December 18, 2018|accessdate=March 24, 2019}}</ref>}}\n|-\n| ''Albumism''\n| Top 50 Albums of 2018\n| {{center|16}}\n| {{center|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.albumism.com/lists/best-albums-of-2018-index|title=Albumism Selects: The 50 Best Albums of 2018|website=Albumism.com|date=November 27, 2018|accessdate=March 24, 2019}}</ref>}}\n|-\n| ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]''\n| Top 20 Albums of 2018\n| {{center|12}}\n| {{center|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/music/2018/12/06/the-20-best-albums-of-2018/|title=The 20 best albums of 2018|website=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=December 6, 2018|accessdate=March 24, 2019}}</ref>}}\n|-\n| ''God Is In The TV''\n| Top 50 Albums of 2018\n| {{center|9}}\n| {{center|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.godisinthetvzine.co.uk/2018/12/10/giittv-album-of-the-year-poll-2018-results-50-1/|title=GIITTV Album Of The Year Poll 2018 Results: 50 -1|website=Godisinthetvzine.co.uk|date=December 10, 2018|accessdate=March 24, 2019}}</ref>}}\n|-\n| ''[[PopMatters]]\n| Top 70 Albums of 2018\n| {{center|25}}\n| {{center|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.popmatters.com/best-albums-of-2018-2622492661.html|title=The 70 Best Albums of 2018|website=[[PopMatters]]|date=December 20, 2018|accessdate=March 24, 2019}}</ref>}}\n|-\n| ''[[Uncut (magazine)|Uncut]]''\n| Top 75 Albums of 2018\n| {{center|12}}\n| {{center|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.albumoftheyear.org/list/1019-uncuts-75-best-albums-of-2018/2|title=Uncut's 75 Best Albums of 2018|website=[[Uncut (magazine)|Uncut]]|accessdate=March 24, 2019}}</ref>}}\n|}\n\n==Track listing==\n{{tracklist\n| all_writing = [[Neko Case]] and Paul Rigby, except where noted\n| total_length = 52:44\n|-\n|title1=Hell-On\n|length1=4:11\n|-\n|title2=Last Lion of Albion\n|writer2= Case, Jeff Galegher, Rigby \n|length2=3:38\n|-\n|title3=Halls of Sarah\n|length3=3:53\n|-\n|title4=Bad Luck\n|length4=3:59\n|-\n|title5=Curse of the I-5 Corridor\n|length5=7:01\n|-\n|title6=Gumball Blue\n|writer6=Case, [[A. C. Newman|Allan Carl Newman]]\n|length6=4:14\n|-\n|title7=Dirty Diamond\n|length7=3:44\n|-\n|title8=Oracle of the Maritimes\n|writer8=Case, [[Laura Veirs]]\n|length8=4:25\n|-\n|title9=Winnie\n|length9=3:54\n|-\n|title10=Sleep All Summer\n|writer10=[[Eric Bachmann]]\n|length10=5:04\n|-\n|title11=My Uncle\u2019s Navy\n|writer11=Case, Newman\n|length11=4:14 \n|-\n|title12=Pitch or Honey\n|length12=4:27\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\n*Neko Case \u2013 vocals, backing vocals, guitar, kalimba, tambourine, clave, piano\n*Paul Rigby \u2013 electric guitar, acoustic guitar, 12-string guitar\n*[[Mark Lanegan]] - duet vocals on \"Curse of the I-5 Corridor\"\n*Eric Bachmann - guitar, duet vocals on \"Sleep All Summer\", piano\n*Rachel Flotard, [[k.d. lang]], [[Kelly Hogan]], [[Laura Veirs]], [[Nora O'Connor]], [[Robert Forster (musician)|Robert Forster]], [[Kathryn Calder]], [[Carl Newman]], Jon Seiders, [[Beth Ditto]] - backing vocals\n*[[Doug Gillard]] - guitar, harpsichord\n*[[Sebastian Steinberg]] - autoharp, electric bass\n*[[Joey Burns]] - upright bass, cello, bass, piano, wurlitzer, pump organ, synthesizer, vibraphone\n*[[Barbara Gruska]] - drums, percussion, drum machine\n*Jeff Galegher - kalimba loop sample, guitar\n*Bj\u00f6rn Yittling - keyboards, bass, guitars\n*[[Steve Berlin]] - saxophone\n*[[Thom Monahan]] - tambourine, tuba\n*Tobias Tagesson - drums\n*Simi Stone - violin, backing vocals\n*[[John Collins (Canadian musician)|John Collins]] - synthesizer\n*Chris Schultz - soundscape, space echo loop\n*[[Matt Chamberlain]] - drums, percussion\n*[[Tom V. Ray]] \u2013 bass\n*Jon Rauhouse \u2013 guitar, pedal steel\n*Dan Hunt - drums, percussion\n*Sandy Schwoebel - bass flute\n*[[Kyle Crane]] - tambourine\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2018)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br /> position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australian Albums ([[ARIA Charts|ARIA]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.auspop.com.au/2018/6/aria-chart-watch-476/|title=ARIA Chart Watch #476|publisher=auspOp|date=June 9, 2018|accessdate=June 9, 2018}}</ref>\n| 88\n|-\n{{album chart|Netherlands|123|artist=Neko Case|album=Hell-On|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 24, 2019}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| New Zealand Heatseeker Albums ([[Recorded Music NZ|RMNZ]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nztop40.co.nz/chart/albums?chart=4487|title=NZ Heatseeker Albums Chart|publisher=[[Recorded Music NZ]]|date=June 11, 2018|accessdate=June 8, 2018}}</ref>\n| 4\n|-\n{{album chart|Scotland|38|date=20180608|rowheader=true|accessdate=June 9, 2018}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Billboard200|31|artist=Neko Case|rowheader=true|accessdate=June 12, 2018}}\n|-\n{{album chart|BillboardFolk|2|artist=Neko Case|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 24, 2019}}\n|-\n{{album chart|BillboardIndependent|4|artist=Neko Case|rowheader=true|accessdate=June 12, 2018}}\n|-\n{{album chart|BillboardAlternative|4|artist=Neko Case|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 24, 2019}}\n|-\n{{album chart|BillboardRock|5|artist=Neko Case|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 24, 2019}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Neko Case}}\n\n[[Category:2018 albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Bj\u00f6rn Yttling]]\n[[Category:Anti- (record label) albums]]\n[[Category:Neko Case albums]]\n\n\n{{2010s-folk-album-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = Hell-O