{"title_page": "A. R. Lakshmanan", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2018}}\n{{Infobox Judge\n| image         = Justice Lakshmanan.jpg\n| name          = Justice A.R. Lakshmanan\n| imagesize     =\n| caption       =\n| office        = [[Judge]] [[Supreme Court of India]]\n| termstart     = 20 December 2002\n| termend       = 22 March 2007\n| nominator     =\n| appointer     =\n| predecessor   =\n| successor     =\n| office2       = [[Law Commission of India|Chairman, 18th Law Commission of India]]\n| termstart2    =2006\n| termend2      =2009\n| nominator2    =\n| appointer2    =\n| predecessor2  =\n| successor2    =\n| birth_date    = {{Birth date and age|1942|03|22|df=y}}\n| birth_place   = [[India]]\n| death_date    =\n| death_place   =\n| spouse        =\n}}\n'''Arunachalam Chettiar Lakshmanan''', [[Bachelor of Arts|B.A.]], [[B.L.]], (born 22 March 1942) is a former [[judge]] of the [[Supreme Court of India]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Suppressing women will affect progress: judge |url=http://www.hinduonnet.com/2003/11/30/stories/2003113003850400.htm |newspaper=[[The Hindu]] |date=2003-11-29 |accessdate=2008-03-24 }}{{Dead link|date=September 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |first=J. |last=Venkatesan |title= Debts Recovery Tribunal gets ISO-9001 certification |url=http://www.hindu.com/2004/08/11/stories/2004081108880400.htm |newspaper=[[The Hindu]] |date=2004-08-10 |accessdate=2008-03-24 | archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080226063052/http://www.hindu.com/2004/08/11/stories/2004081108880400.htm| archivedate= 26 February 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref>\n\nHe studied in [[Chennai]] ([[Madras]]). Before his elevation to the Supreme Court in 2002, he served as a judge on the [[Madras High Court]] and [[Kerala High Court]]. He was also appointed as Chief Justice of [[Rajasthan High Court]] in 2000 and [[Andhra Pradesh High Court]] in 2001. He retired in 2007.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.supremecourtofindia.nic.in/judges/bio/arl.htm |title=Hon'ble Dr. Justice AR. Lakshmanan |accessdate=2008-03-24 |publisher=[[Supreme Court of India]] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080220181513/http://www.supremecourtofindia.nic.in/judges/bio/arl.htm |archivedate=20 February 2008 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nHe hails from the [[Nagarathar]] community and his native is Devakottai, Tamil Nadu. He served as chairman of the [[Law Commission of India]] during 2006\u20132009. He is representing Tamil Nadu in the Mullai Periyar Panel appointed by the Hon'ble Supreme Court of India. The panel is headed by Justice A.S.Anand.\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lakshmanan, A. R.}}\n[[Category:1942 births]]\n[[Category:Justices of the Supreme Court of India]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:St. Joseph's College, Tiruchirappalli alumni]]\n[[Category:Chief Justices of the Rajasthan High Court]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian judges]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian judges]]\n[[Category:Politicians from Chennai]]\n[[Category:Chief Justices of the Kerala High Court]]\n\n\n{{India-law-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2018}}\n{{Infobox Judge\n| image         = Justice Lakshmanan.jpg\n| name          = Justice A.R. Lakshmanan\n| imagesize     =\n| caption       =\n| office        = [[Judge]] [[Supreme Court of India]]\n| termstart     = 20 December 2002\n| termend       = 22 March 2007\n| nominator     =\n| appointer     =\n| predecessor   =\n| successor     =\n| office2       = [[Law Commission of India|Chairman, 18th Law Commission of India]]\n| termstart2    =2006\n| termend2      =2009\n| nominator2    =\n| appointer2    =\n| predecessor2  =\n| successor2    =\n| birth_date    = {{Birth date and age|1942|03|22|df=y}}\n| birth_place   = [[India]]\n| death_date    =\n| death_place   =\n| spouse        =\n}}\n'''Arunachalam Chettiar Lakshmanan''', [[Bachelor of Arts|B.A.]], [[B.L.]], (born 22 March 1942) is a former [[judge]] of the [[Supreme Court of India]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Suppressing women will affect progress: judge |url=http://www.hinduonnet.com/2003/11/30/stories/2003113003850400.htm |newspaper=[[The Hindu]] |date=2003-11-29 |accessdate=2008-03-24 }}{{Dead link|date=September 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |first=J. |last=Venkatesan |title= Debts Recovery Tribunal gets ISO-9001 certification |url=http://www.hindu.com/2004/08/11/stories/2004081108880400.htm |newspaper=[[The Hindu]] |date=2004-08-10 |accessdate=2008-03-24 | archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080226063052/http://www.hindu.com/2004/08/11/stories/2004081108880400.htm| archivedate= 26 February 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref>\n\nHe studied in [[Chennai]] ([[Madras]]). Before his elevation to the Supreme Court in 2002, he served as a judge on the [[Madras High Court]] and [[Kerala High Court]]. He was also appointed as Chief Justice of [[Rajasthan High Court]] in 2000 and [[Andhra Pradesh High Court]] in 2001. He retired in 2007.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.supremecourtofindia.nic.in/judges/bio/arl.htm |title=Hon'ble Dr. Justice AR. Lakshmanan |accessdate=2008-03-24 |publisher=[[Supreme Court of India]] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080220181513/http://www.supremecourtofindia.nic.in/judges/bio/arl.htm |archivedate=20 February 2008 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nHe hails from the [[Nagarathar]] community and his native is Devakottai, Tamil Nadu. He served as chairman of the [[Law Commission of India]] during 2006-2009. He is representing Tamil Nadu in the Mullai Periyar Panel appointed by the Hon'ble Supreme Court of India. The panel is headed by Justice A.S.Anand.\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lakshmanan, A. R.}}\n[[Category:1942 births]]\n[[Category:Justices of the Supreme Court of India]]\n[[Category:Living people]]